---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<section class="intro">
				<h1>Hi, I'm Yadvendra.</h1>
				<p class="lede">
					I build AI systems for production. I'm currently Head of AI and co-founder at
					<a href="https://www.aaysanalytics.com/">Aays Analytics</a>, where I lead forward-deployed engineering on
					LLM-powered agents, retrieval pipelines, and evaluation harnesses for enterprise clients.
				</p>
				<p>
					Previously, I have co-founded <a href="https://fabrichq.ai/">Fabric</a> and <a href="https://aidetic.in/">Aidetic</a> where I set-up AI and Data teams from scratch and delivered AI solutions to enterprise clients.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<p>
					Over the last five years I've grown Aidetic from zero to a 65-person team, doubled revenue
					year-over-year for three consecutive years, and shipped agentic systems across fintech,
					SaaS, oil &amp; gas, and banking. During this time I also co-founded
					Fabric (at that point D2C e-commerce AI), worked on
					enterprise Q&amp;A systems at Nesh, and started out doing data science at Coviam and ZS
					Associates.
				</p>
				<p>
					What I care about most: agent architectures that actually work in production,
					tool-use design, context engineering, evaluation, cost and latency, and the
					human-in-the-loop guardrails that make all of it safe to deploy.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>What I'm working on</h2>
				<ul>
					<li>
						An agent-factory platform that lets 400+ business users at a Docomo Group
						retail company spin up LLM agents over 1,200+ data tables.
					</li>
					<li>
						An <a href="https://github.com/minas-ai/haki">agent harness</a> to improve their performance and replicating agentic architectures for clients at scale and speed.
					</li>
					<li>
						The strategic <a href="https://www.databricks.com/">Databricks</a> partnership at Aidetic;
						training curricula, client workshops, and a migration accelerator that
						speeds up competitive migrations by ~40%.
					</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<section>
				<p>
					More about my <a href="/about">background</a>, or find me on
					<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/yadvendra-kshatri-28137a88/">LinkedIn</a>
					and <a href="https://github.com/ydvnkshatri">GitHub</a>. The
					<a href="/blog">blog</a> is where I'll write up things I've learned along the way (just starting it first time...).
				</p>
			</section>
		</main>
		<Footer />
		<style>
			.intro {
				margin-top: 1em;
				margin-bottom: 2em;
			}
			.intro h1 {
				margin-bottom: 0.4em;
			}
			.lede {
				font-size: 1.2em;
				color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
			}
			section {
				margin-bottom: 1.5em;
			}
			section h2 {
				font-size: 1.563em;
				margin-top: 1em;
			}
			ul {
				padding-left: 1.2em;
			}
			ul li {
				margin-bottom: 0.6em;
			}
		</style>
	</body>
</html>
